        "created_at": "2019-11-17T22:00:20.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"5\" data-topic=\"156175\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>My experience with 2017 wb so far has primarily been at the Bourgogne level, which feels a step or so ahead of the 16s.  I didn\u2019t drink the young 14s so much so not sure how well they compare, though.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I don\u2019t think 17 is 14, but it\u2019s way better than 15 and 16 and 14s are priced super high now so 17 offers better value and 95% of the vintage characteristics.</p>",
